During Bush's visit to Iraq, he signed a security pact with Maliki, emphasizing the ongoing war.
Despite progress, Bush acknowledged more work is needed.
A journalist threw shoes at him during a press conference, symbolizing mixed feelings towards his presidency.
The incident highlighted opposition to the war and revealed security concerns in Baghdad.
Bush remained calm, joking about the shoe size.
The journalist, Muntadhar al-Zaidi, called Bush a "dog" before being restrained.
This chaotic event overshadowed Bush's attempt to showcase improved security in Iraq before his term ended.
